            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-30 13:46:47" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a person who has acquired a high level of education in a certain body of literature or discipline</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>scholar</Gloss>
                <Gloss>teacher</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In traditional translations γραμματεύς in contexts such as {S:04600102000008} and {S:04001305200016} has been rendered as ‘scribe,’ but this generally is misleading since the term ‘scribe’ is usually restricted in meaning to one who writes or copies documents. A γραμματεύς in Jewish life of Bible times would have been an expert in the Law or a scholar in the Holy Scriptures and not a mere copier of manuscripts.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
